# Exploration: find

## Test scope
  43 behavioral groups: 29 unique, 14 shared

## Observed: 4/4 flags
  4 uniquely observable, 0 distinguishable via flag pairs
  1 behavioral aliases (different flags, identical behavior)
  robustness: 4 verified in all contexts, 0 in most, 0 context-dependent

## Unique behavior (observable when tested alone)
  -D
    tested: "-D" "input.txt" "other.txt" in words_minimal
    | flag removes 1 lines: input.txt
    | 1 lines unchanged
    | stderr: find: Ignoring unrecognised debug flag 'input.txt'
    without flag:
      input.txt
      other.txt
    with flag:
      other.txt
  -N
    tested: "-N" in words_standard
    | flag removes 12 lines: ., ./b.txt, ./exec.sh, ./a.txt, ./input.txt
    | exit: 0 → 1
    | stderr: find: unknown predicate `-N'
    without flag:
      .
      ./b.txt
      ./exec.sh
      ./a.txt
      ./input.txt
      ./subdir
            ... (6 more)
    with flag:
  -a
    tested: "-a" in words_standard
    | flag removes 12 lines: ., ./b.txt, ./exec.sh, ./a.txt, ./input.txt
    | exit: 0 → 1
    | stderr: find: invalid expression
    | you have used a binary operator '-a' with nothing before it.
    without flag:
      .
      ./b.txt
      ./exec.sh
      ./a.txt
      ./input.txt
      ./subdir
            ... (6 more)
    with flag:
  -name
    tested: "." "-name" "*.txt" in passwd_minimal
    | stdout: 2 lines
    | exit 0
    without flag:
    with flag:
      ./input.txt
      ./other.txt
  -o
    tested: "-o" in words_standard
    | flag removes 12 lines: ., ./b.txt, ./exec.sh, ./a.txt, ./input.txt
    | exit: 0 → 1
    | stderr: find: invalid expression
    | you have used a binary operator '-o' with nothing before it.
    without flag:
      .
      ./b.txt
      ./exec.sh
      ./a.txt
      ./input.txt
      ./subdir
            ... (6 more)
    with flag:
  -type
    tested: "." "-type" "f" in words_standard
    | stdout: 9 lines
    | exit 0
    without flag:
    with flag:
      ./b.txt
      ./exec.sh
      ./a.txt
      ./input.txt
      ./subdir/nested.txt
      ./readonly.dat
            ... (3 more)

## Distinguishable in combination (verified via flag pairs)
  -print
    | flag removes 3 lines: ., ./input.txt, ./other.txt
    | exit: 0 → 1
    | stderr: find: paths must precede expression: `.'
    proven via: "-D" "." "-print"

